It tells me what’s right and what’s not, when to leave and where to go. It’s not Shakespeare; it does not speak in memorable lines. My inner voice always gives it to me straight. Tells me who my real friends are, when to say yes, when to say no, whether the person sitting next to me is the one I’ll be spending the rest of my life with.

